		<description><![CDATA[Stair lifts come in all shapes and sizes, as stairlift producers understand the ever varying shapes and sizes of the household staircase. If you&#8217;re looking for a stair lift, then you should not be put off by concerns over your staircase. Nearly every staircase is suitable, as stair lifts are highly adaptable options. With various [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Stair lifts come in all shapes and sizes, as <a href="http://thecci.org/are-products-targeting-an-older-population-set-for-a-boom/">stairlift producers</a> understand the ever varying shapes and sizes of the household staircase. If you&#8217;re looking for a stair lift, then you should not be put off by concerns over your staircase.</strong></p>
<p>Nearly every staircase is suitable, as stair lifts are highly adaptable options. With various forms and models of lifts on the market, there is usually something to suit your needs.</p>
<p><strong>Fitting the stair lift</strong></p>
<p>Stair lifts are designed to fit on the staircase without getting in the way. The rail is the primary part of the lift, and will skirt along the side. If there are any corners in the stairs, such as a typical right angled corner, the rail can be curved around to allow the chair to move over this.</p>
<p>Likewise, the chair itself simply sits on the rail, and is often collapsible. This ensures less space is used when the chair is not in use. With narrow chairs designed to save extra space, the combination of chair and rail do not actually get in the way.</p>
<p>When not in use, the stairs can still be used as a normal stair case. Itâ€™s understandable that not everyone in a given household may need to use the lift, so allowing for both parties is a huge priority.</p>
<p><strong>Usage and continual support</strong></p>
<p>Furthermore, stairlifts are easy to use, designed to be highly usable. The simple controls mean there isn&#8217;t a rulebook to learn, just deciding whether you want to go up or down is usually enough. The stairlift itself will most commonly run on battery power.</p>
<p>This can be charged up when not in use, but the battery usually lasts for a few hours usage; this ensures that the lift will still work in the event of a power cut, so that you&#8217;re not stuck upstairs or on the chair in an emergency.</p>
<p>Additionally, you don&#8217;t need to worry about anything going wrong or any maintenance issues. <a href="http://thecci.org/are-products-targeting-an-older-population-set-for-a-boom/">Stannah stair lifts</a> provide excellent and continual customer support; if you have any stair lift issues, they will be happy to help.</p>
