		<title>Problems with home economics could contribute to poor health</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RadioStorytime/~3/PnXQ6K-Y6zg/</link>
		<comments>http://www.radiostorytime.com/health-info/problems-with-home-economics-could-contribute-to-poor-health/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 29 May 2012 06:00:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>mzPOTTER</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Health Info]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Problems with home economics could contribute to poor health]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.radiostorytime.com/?p=1369</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Economic concerns, responsibilities at work, family commitments and the need to make ends meet making ends meet, may be putting your health at risk. This was highlighted by a recent study developed by U.S. researchers. Here we have more details and some tips to manage stress related to the household economy. Some people work to [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://c713371.r71.cf2.rackcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/iStock_000013861844XSmall_hundreddays-e1304882627658.jpg" alt="Problems with home economics could contribute to poor health" align="left" style="padding-right:5px" width="200"/>Economic concerns, responsibilities at work, family commitments and the need to make ends meet making ends meet, may be putting your health at risk. This was highlighted by a recent study developed by U.S. researchers. Here we have more details and some tips to manage stress related to the household economy.</p>
<p>Some people work to live and others live to work. Those that follow the second case, sometimes they do by vocation but many actually do under pressure. Daily expenses, taxes and services, food, school for boys, clothes, let alone outputs whether to pay the rent or the rent. All these things increase the amount of money needed to bring the desired lifestyle. So many people end up immersed in work, getting obsessed with money and quiet come to meet, or simply make ends meet and fulfill.</p>
<p>But this situation is stressful for anyone and if it continues over time can be harmful to health. In this regard, a study by researchers at the Center for Advancing Health, located in Washington, USA, analyzed the response of more than 10 000 respondents in Pennsylvania in 2008 and found that more than a quarter of those who declared having a bad economic situation described their health as poor or fair.<span id="more-1369"></span></p>
<p>Moreover, among people who had difficulty paying for housing had more cases of high blood pressure and arthritis, and the difference was noticeable among people who had to pay rent and those who owned the property.</p>
<p>In this modern society where time is money and the priority is to be productive is easy to fall into the oblivion of our vital needs, including rest, leisure time and entertainment.</p>
<p>The body needs to be safe and it is necessary to maintain a balanced life, accompanied with a healthy diet and, if possible, an exercise routine (and if outdoors, better, and they say that being in contact with the nature and see the green plants, is good for lowering stress and maintain high self-esteem).</p>
<p>But in the rush to meet and do everything, whether at work or at home, they often lose sight of the fact that along with the duties and responsibilities also increases the level of stress and productivity plummets: Stress can destroy your ability to concentrate, getting angry, depressed and even affect your personal and professional relationships.</p>
<p>In addition, stress can weaken your immune system, which increases your vulnerability to getting a wide variety of diseases, from allergies, colds and back pain to depression, heart problems and other chronic conditions. Therefore, it is important to recognize if they have a situation of prolonged stress that never ends, so you can take charge of the problem and find a solution. And if you do not succeed on your own, it is important that you seek professional help.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, here are some recommendations that could help control stress related to money and your home economics:</p>
<p>- Try to take a five minute break for tea and be sure to take breaks to relax and replenish energy.<br />
- Do not panic at the negative stories you hear every day in newspapers and on television. Try to think positive and look for opportunities.<br />
- Try to change the way things once and find opportunities for growth and real change in the challenges. We know the old saying that in every crisis there is always a chance, try to find it and take it.<br />
Identify the things that create stress related to finances and evaluates the ways in which you and your family can reduce expenses or manage finances more efficiently.<br />
- Pay attention to how you choose to control your stress and look for healthier ways. Many people are inclined to unhealthy behaviors like smoking, drinking alcohol, gambling money or eat in large quantities, others also tend to argue with their partners or other members of the family environment. If this is your case, do not let it get worse and consider seeking professional help.<br />
- Look for ways you can motivate economic difficulties in finding healthy ways to cope with stress. For example, try taking a walk (it&#8217;s a cheap way to exercise), dinner at home with your family (estrecharÃ¡s save money and bonds), take a course or find activities sponsored low-cost or free in your area.</p>
<p>The key is to use the time to be creative and try new strategies to manage your life, and avoid despair. Think that all you can do today will be like seeds that will eventually bear fruit. And the crisis may go faster than you think.</p>
<p>Remember that work is only one of the important aspects of your life and above all you must stay strong and healthy to meet all your responsibilities. Do not forget to take care of your health and your emotions are essential when thinking about a life in balance and harmony.</p>
