		<title>Aerobic exercise is more effective in reducing belly fat</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/RadioStorytime/~3/bCRyYBpdb9Q/</link>
		<comments>http://www.radiostorytime.com/fitness-2/aerobic-exercise-is-more-effective-in-reducing-belly-fat/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 15 May 2012 06:00:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>mzPOTTER</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Fitness]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Aerobic exercise]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Aerobic exercise is more effective in reducing belly fat]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Exercise]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[reducing belly fat]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.radiostorytime.com/?p=1360</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[To remove those extra kilos or pounds that have accumulated in your body, aerobic exercise have proved more effective than resistance. Here&#8217;s what we found a group of U.S. researchers about it, and why reduce abdominal fat is more than a cosmetic issue. At that aerobic exercise appear to be more effective when looking for [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://c713371.r71.cf2.rackcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/iStock_000014158831XSmall_-Stockphoto4u.jpg" alt="Aerobic exercise is more effective in reducing belly fat" align="left" style="padding-right:5px" width="200"/>To remove those extra kilos or pounds that have accumulated in your body, aerobic exercise have proved more effective than resistance. Here&#8217;s what we found a group of U.S. researchers about it, and why reduce abdominal fat is more than a cosmetic issue.</p>
<p>At that aerobic exercise appear to be more effective when looking for a flat stomach and intestine. That had been shown in some studies (we informed you earlier in this article vidaysalud.com other), and return it to confirm a new research by specialists Medical Center Duke University in the United States, which was published in the August 25 issue of the American Journal of Physiology.</p>
<p>According to the latter work, aerobic exercise can burn 67 percent more calories than resistance training. To reach these results, the researchers compared the efficacy of aerobic exercise (like jogging) with resistance training (weight lifting) or a combination of both activities in 196 overweight, sedentary adults, aged 18 to 70 years age, for eight months.<span id="more-1360"></span></p>
<p>Participants in the aerobic group trotted the equivalent of 19 kilometers or 12 miles per week, 80 percent of maximum heart rate, while members of the resistance group did three sets of twelve repetitions, three times a week.</p>
<p>Thus, researchers looked at how these types of exercise reduced the fat found deep in the abdomen and fills the spaces between the internal organs, called visceral fat and liver, which is associated with an increased risk of developing heart disease, diabetes and some cancers.</p>
<p>After analyzing the data, found that aerobic exercise significantly reduced visceral fat and liver and improved risk factors for heart disease and diabetes and insulin resistance, liver enzymes and triglycerides. By contrast, resistance training did not confer these benefits but the combination of both years did achieve similar results.</p>
<p>Thus, aerobic exercise or a combination of both, as Paul and Rocio are doing, not only can help you lose those extra kilos or pounds but also to combat all the health problems that are associated with excess abdominal fat .</p>
<p>The exercises are an important part of your health, and if you accompany a healthy diet appropriate for your height and activity level will be much more effective. Supplement your exercise routine with proper diet: rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lowfat dairy, fish, poultry, lean meats, etc.. that is not too low in calories so you have enough energy and strength to exercise. Remember to drink plenty of water to stay well hydrated. Alongside all this, do not forget to rest enough. You see how your body shows the difference, not only more energy but with a much flatter stomach, which also is healthier.</p>
