			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://c713371.r71.cf2.rackcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/iStock_000017143674XSmall_Vicki-Reid1.jpg" alt="Exercise to prevent cancer" align="left" style="padding-right:5px" width="200"/>Doing regular exercise can reduce up to 35 percent the chances of developing colon cancer and breast cancer by 25 percent. So found a study that confirms the relationship between physical inactivity and cancer and provides new data in order to reduce the risk of this disease with healthier lifestyles. If your favorite pastime is to sit comfortably on a couch watching TV for hours, you&#8217;re passing it an unnecessary invitation to cancer. CiÃ©rrale the door by putting your body in motion, even during work hours.</p>
<p>Monday to Friday and sometimes Saturday, Raul gets up early, leaves home and takes the bus that takes him to his job sitting where he spends eight to nine hours sitting at a desk. When finished, take the bus again and when he comes home he loves to sit back watch a movie while you dine. Then she lays down and the next day everything starts again. Do you find it known this routine?</p>
<p>If your habits are similar, you have to start considering the possibility of adding more movement to your life. Doing regular exercise you can improve your quality of life and stay healthier longer.<span id="more-1356"></span></p>
<p>Physical activity not only helps relieve back pain or symptoms of fibromyalgia, but also allows you to maintain a healthy heart. If one analyzes the results of different studies that confirm to sit for hours watching TV can raise blood pressure, something that endangers the health of your heart. In this muscle as it puts a heavy burden worker inactivity: just look at a paper in which we explain to sit for a long time may increase the chances that you suffer a heart attack.</p>
<p>The danger of inaction is alarming when one considers that according to the researchers calculated, people sit for 15.5 hours each day, including meals, travel to and from work or school, working on the computer and watch TV. Office workers, for example, spend 75 percent of the time sitting.</p>
<p>A new study by researchers at Cancer Care of Health Services in Calgary Alberta, Canada, has found an association between physical inactivity and cancer development, another negative consequence of inactivity.</p>
<p>But there are solutions. According to the study, published in the October issue of the journal Cancer Prevention Research, regular exercise can reduce the risk of developing colon cancer by up to 35 percent. The same goes for breast cancer, whose risk can be reduced up to 25 percent through exercise.</p>
<p>Even when you must sit many hours, as happens to Raul, just take a few minutes recurrent breaks to walk may be helpful, both to maintain the health of your heart to prevent cancer.</p>
<p>Therefore, some recommendations to combat sedentary work are:</p>
<p>- Get up several times to serve water or another beverage like tea or coffee (avoid soda and sugary drinks).<br />
- Receive phone calls to the feet.<br />
- Walk to where you will find a partner of work instead of calling or send an e-mail.<br />
- If you work driving a car, be sure to stop a few minutes every so often to take a short walk and stretch your legs.<br />
- Go pick out your copies or prints you did, instead of asking someone to bring you the your office.<br />
- If you can, stands at a meeting or conference.<br />
- If you work at home, stop going to the bathroom, to go to the kitchen to the stairs or walk around the house.</p>
<p>And if all this, plus, you add an exercise routine a little more intense with healthy habits in your diet, you&#8217;ll gain health and quality of life. Cheer up! With a few small changes you can tell the difference.</p>
